<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF616ADEFD1494031A5DB809" pageId="154" pageNumber="915" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF616ADEFD1494031A5DB809" blockId="154.[692,1334,445,867]" pageId="154" pageNumber="915">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF616ADEFD1494031DEEB945" box="[744,1006,602,631]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="915" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annamitica">Murina annamitica</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF616ADEFC7594241DEFB9AC" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1891" box="[905,1007,637,670]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="915" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="feae">M. feae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF616ADEFBBB94241AEEB9AC" box="[1095,1262,637,670]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="915" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beelzebub">M. beelzebub</taxonomicName>
, but other studies placed it close to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF616ADEFB6794FD1D1EB9DF" authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1964" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="918" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peninsularis">M. peninsularis</taxonomicName>
. Morphologically, it is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF616ADEFCE894AD1DA1B827" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1872" box="[788,929,756,789]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="154" pageNumber="917" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyclotis">M. cyclotis</taxonomicName>
and its relatives including M. perunsularis. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
